>Description:
I have installed the ubuntu "gutsy gibbon" i386 linux distribution, apt-get installed drscheme, opened the help desk and searched for "set-pixel".

There was a search result containing the search query, and when I clicked on the corresponding hyperlink to read the documentation for "set-pixel", drscheme asked me wether I wanted to view the online documentation that contained this function, or if it should download and install the missing documentation.
I chose to download and install the missing documentation. The download & installation process terminated successfully, but after clicking on the search results again, the plt webserver sends an error page stating that the requested document could not be found.
